-- 
Venizelos Welcomes German Approval of European Rescue Fund

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-09-29T15:11:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/venizelos-welcomes-german-approval-of-european-rescue-fund.html
Greek Finance Minister Evangelos
Venizelos welcomed the German parliament’s approval of the
European Financial Stability Facility’s expanded powers,
according to an e-mailed statement from the Athens-based
ministry today.  Venizelos said decisions reached at a July 21 European
Union summit are of “vital” importance for the euro and the
euro area and that  Greece  has sent “clear and decisive”
signals that it will fulfill its commitments to its EU partners
and its creditors, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  